The paper deals with the Independent Cascade Model (ICM) which is a model for information diffusion in social networks and complex networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The problem studied in the paper involves selecting a set of initial seeds and buying links to maximize the information diffusion, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also deals with the dynamics of information diffusion in social networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) sub-category. The paper proposes approximation algorithms for the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and approximation techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
